Australia: The completion of the railway network between Adelaide, Brisbane, Melbourne and Sydney.
Sir Henry Parkes delivered the Tenterfield Oration.
Brazil: Field Marshal Deodoro da Fonseca organizes a military coup which deposes Emperor Pedro II of Brazil and abolishes the Brazilian monarchy. Deodoro da Fonseca proclaims Brazil a Republic and forms a Provisional Government.
The Brazilian Imperial Family is forced into exile in France.
The modern-day flag of Brazil is adopted by the Provisional Government of the Republic.
Argentina is the first country to recognize the abolition of the monarchy in Brazil.
Colombia: Foundation of Villa Holguin (Later Armenia, Colombia ) by Jesus Maria Ocampo
The Thousand Days War (1899–1902) (Spanish: Guerra de los Mil Días)
Estonia: Policy of Russification introduced where Baltic German legal and educational institutions are abolished or transformed into Russian
France: The Eiffel Tower is opened to the public.
The Eiffel Tower lifts begin service.
Haiti: President Légitime is overthrown; the Constituent Assembly installs a provisional government
The Constituent Assembly elects Florvil Hyppolite to a seven-year term as president
India: Keshav Baliram Hedgewar(1 April 1889 – 21 June 1940) was the founding Sarsanghachalak of the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh (RSS). Hedgewar founded the RSS in Nagpur in 1925, with the intention of promoting the concept of a united India rooted in indigenous ideology.[1] He drew upon influences from the Congress Party to start the RSS as a reaction to the Malabar riots.[2] Khudiram Bose is born (to 1908)
Italy: Somalia is established as the second Italian colony in Africa.
Serbia: King Milan Obrenović abdicates the throne in favour of his minor (age) son Aleksandar Obrenović. Austrophile policy continues.
Slovenia: Strike of coal miners in the Central Sava Valley in Zagorje and Trbovlje.
Sweden: The Social Democratic Party is founded.
USA: North Dakota, South Dakota becomes the 39th and 40th states.
Johnstown flood of 1889: A dam failure and fire in Pennsylvania.
Land Run of 1889: The land run begins.
